527
00:24:08,145 --> 00:24:11,748
I know we don't like
the idea of death.

528
00:24:11,749 --> 00:24:13,783
-I know what you're getting at.
-But you lose something

529
00:24:13,784 --> 00:24:14,985
by getting rid of death.

530
00:24:14,986 --> 00:24:16,586
Yeah, we'll lose something

531
00:24:16,587 --> 00:24:18,288
like we lost something
when we got rid of slavery

532
00:24:18,289 --> 00:24:20,056
or smallpox.

533
00:24:20,057 --> 00:24:22,926
So I think people...

534
00:24:22,927 --> 00:24:25,762
people are tying themselves
in knots to rationalize death.

535
00:24:25,763 --> 00:24:27,531
I believe that,
right now,

536
00:24:27,532 --> 00:24:29,533
we're kind of in
this tragic situation where,

537
00:24:29,534 --> 00:24:31,268
over time, hopefully
you kind of learn.

538
00:24:31,269 --> 00:24:32,702
Your wisdom grows over time.

539
00:24:32,703 --> 00:24:34,104
At the same time,

540
00:24:34,105 --> 00:24:35,972
your cognitive and physical
health is declining.

541
00:24:35,973 --> 00:24:38,241
That really sucks.
That's a bad situation.

542
00:24:38,242 --> 00:24:40,176
What if they both could keep
going up indefinitely?

543
00:24:40,177 --> 00:24:42,212
So you could live for hundreds
of years or longer,

544
00:24:42,213 --> 00:24:44,848
and get smarter, and more
knowledgeable, and wiser.

545
00:24:44,849 --> 00:24:47,083
Hopefully more mature,
and have more foresight

546
00:24:47,084 --> 00:24:49,553
because you got a much longer
planning horizon.

547
00:24:49,554 --> 00:24:51,922
What we'll have is a world
of, I call, ultra-mature people,

548
00:24:51,923 --> 00:24:53,690
which I think will actually
be a better world

549
00:24:53,691 --> 00:24:55,158
than the one
we have today.

550
00:24:55,159 --> 00:24:57,827
And if they say, well--
And this comes up all the time.

551
00:24:57,828 --> 00:24:59,996
They say, "Well, death is what
